cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.RO

The paper presents a neural network model that learns to generate novel structured behaviors in an unstructured environment through curiosity-driven intrinsic motivation. This involves learning a world model predicting the consequences of actions and taking actions that challenge the model, leading to exploration and discovery of informative interactions with the environment. The paper involves machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and robotics (cs.RO) as it deals with learning from visual input and generating motor actions in a simulated environment. Additionally, the paper involves neural networks and reinforcement learning, which are common in the above-mentioned sub-categories.
